    <a href="#api">§7 API Reference</a>
  </nav>

  <div class="dp-main">

    <%# ── §1 Overview ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="overview">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§1</div>
        <h2>System Overview</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="dp-callout dp-danger">
        <span class="dp-ci">⛔</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Read-Only Integrity Mandate:</strong> The Audit tab is strictly read-only.
          No operator may modify, delete, or re-order any entry in the Audit Event Registry
          or Node Activity Log. All records are append-only. Any write attempt from this
          tab returns <code>HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed</code> at the API boundary.
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        The Audit &amp; Reports tab is the Forensic Workstation of the bearerCORE™ CBDC platform.
        It provides a three-pane interface — Forensic Filters &amp; Health (left), Dual-Ledger Event
        Tables (centre), and Forensic Evidence &amp; Reporting (right) — through which central bank
        auditors investigate monetary events, verify cryptographic evidence, and produce legally
        certified compliance documents.
      </p>
      <p>
        The workstation implements a <strong>Dual-Registry Architecture</strong>. The top table
        (<strong>Audit Event Registry</strong>) surfaces macro-monetary events: issuances, redemptions,
        large-scale transfers, and burns. The bottom table (<strong>Node Activity &amp; System Logs</strong>)
        surfaces operational events: operator logins, node state changes, and system-level alerts.
        The two ledgers are cross-searched when filters are applied, and a single row selection in
        either table instantly populates the right-pane evidence panel.
      </p>

      <div class="dp-pane-grid">
        <div class="dp-pane dp-pane-left">
          <h3>Left Pane — Forensic Filters &amp; Health</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Monetary Health Ribbon: Supply Integrity %, Pending Anchorings, Active Alerts</li>
            <li>Standard filters: Jurisdiction, Operator ID, Institution, Corridor, Status</li>
            <li>Forensic filters: Velocity Anomaly toggle, Min Value threshold, Alert Status</li>
            <li>Apply Filter — cross-registry search across both ledgers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-pane dp-pane-middle">
          <h3>Centre Pane — Dual Ledger View</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Audit Event Registry (top): Timestamp, Event Type, Reference ID, Operator, Institution, Amount</li>
            <li>Node Activity &amp; System Logs (bottom): Timestamp, Event Type, Reference ID, Operator, Institution, Status</li>
            <li>Row selection → instant right-pane evidence population</li>
            <li>Per-table Refresh and Export Registry buttons</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-pane dp-pane-right">
          <h3>Right Pane — Forensic Evidence &amp; Reporting</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Event ID, Event Type, Amount fields</li>
            <li>Manifest Hash and Ed25519 Signature read-only fields</li>
            <li>DLT Anchor TX reference</li>
            <li>HSM Validation badge (VALIDATED / NOT VALIDATED)</li>
            <li>Four-Eyes Authorizer IDs (Authorizer 1 &amp; 2)</li>
            <li>Verify Signature — real-time Ed25519 check vs. DLT record</li>
            <li>Reporting: Export CSV, Certified Audit Statement (PDF), Compliance Report, DLT Snapshot Anchor</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Tab Read-Only Contract</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>Permitted</th><th>Rationale</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>View audit events</td><td><span class="dp-badge green">YES</span></td><td>Core auditor function</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Filter / search events</td><td><span class="dp-badge green">YES</span></td><td>Core auditor function</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Verify signature</td><td><span class="dp-badge green">YES</span></td><td>Read-only public-key check</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Export CSV / PDF</td><td><span class="dp-badge green">YES</span></td><td>Output only, no DB write</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Generate compliance report</td><td><span class="dp-badge green">YES</span></td><td>Creates <code>AuditReport</code> record (append-only)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Anchor snapshot to DLT</td><td><span class="dp-badge amber">LEAD ADMIN</span></td><td>Creates immutable <code>AuditSnapshot</code> — append-only</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Edit any event field</td><td><span class="dp-badge red">NO</span></td><td>Append-only registry</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Delete any event</td><td><span class="dp-badge red">NO</span></td><td>Immutability guarantee</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>
    </div>

    <%# ── §2 Data Models ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="data-models">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§2</div>
        <h2>Architecture &amp; Data Models</h2>
      </div>

      <p>
        Four models compose the Dual-Registry Architecture. <strong>AuditEvent</strong> is the
        primary immutable ledger. <strong>AuditSnapshot</strong> captures DLT-anchored hashes
        at a point in time. <strong>AuditReport</strong> tracks generated compliance documents.
        <strong>IssuerKey</strong> (shared with the Issuance tab) provides the Ed25519 public keys
        used for signature verification — no private key material is ever loaded in this tab.
      </p>

      <h3>AuditEvent</h3>
      <p>
        The primary append-only ledger record. Covers every macro-monetary and node-activity event
        in the system. The <code>event_type</code> enum determines which table panel the event
        appears in.
      </p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">id</td><td class="t">uuid</td><td>Primary key — immutable event identifier</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">event_type</td><td class="t">enum</td><td><code>issuance</code> | <code>burn</code> | <code>liquidity_lock</code> | <code>governance</code> | <code>validation</code> | <code>destruction</code> | <code>anchor</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">reference_id</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Cross-reference to source record (e.g. batch ID, transfer ID)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">operator</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Operator ID who triggered the event</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">institution</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Commercial bank or central bank name</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">jurisdiction</td><td class="t">string</td><td>ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 country code (e.g. <code>KEN</code>, <code>NGA</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">corridor</td><td class="t">string</td><td>FX corridor reference (e.g. <code>NGA-KEN</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">amount</td><td class="t">bigint</td><td>Event monetary value in minor currency units (avoids float precision)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">status</td><td class="t">enum</td><td><code>pending</code> | <code>completed</code> | <code>failed</code> | <code>flagged</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">manifest_hash</td><td class="t">string</td><td>SHA-256 of the event payload — used for Ed25519 signature verification</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">signature</td><td class="t">text</td><td>Ed25519 Base64URL signature over <code>manifest_hash</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">dlt_anchor_tx</td><td class="t">string</td><td>DLT transaction ID if this event was individually anchored</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">payload</td><td class="t">jsonb</td><td>Full event payload — includes <code>authorizer_1</code>, <code>authorizer_2</code>, <code>hsm_validated</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">created_at</td><td class="t">timestamp</td><td>Immutable event timestamp (UTC)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <div class="dp-callout dp-info" style="margin-top:12px;">
        <span class="dp-ci">ℹ</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Dual-Ledger Routing:</strong> The Qt UI routes events to the correct table
          panel based on <code>event_type</code>. Macro-monetary types
          (<code>issuance</code>, <code>burn</code>, <code>liquidity_lock</code>, <code>destruction</code>)
          appear in the <strong>Audit Event Registry</strong> (top table, shows Amount).
          Operational types (<code>governance</code>, <code>validation</code>, <code>anchor</code>)
          appear in the <strong>Node Activity &amp; System Logs</strong> table (bottom, shows Status).
          Both tables share the same API response — the Qt controller populates both simultaneously.
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>AuditSnapshot</h3>
      <p>
        Created when a Lead Administrator anchors the current audit state to the DLT.
        The <code>snapshot_hash</code> is a SHA-256 Merkle-style chain digest over all
        <code>AuditEvent</code> records up to the anchor time, ordered by <code>id</code>.
        Once written, this record is never updated.
      </p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">id</td><td class="t">uuid</td><td>Primary key</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">snapshot_hash</td><td class="t">string</td><td>SHA-256 chain digest over all events up to anchor time</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">dlt_tx_id</td><td class="t">string</td><td>DLT transaction identifier returned by the ledger node</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">jurisdiction</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Optional jurisdiction scope for the snapshot</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">anchored_by</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Operator ID of the Lead Administrator who triggered anchoring</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">anchored_at</td><td class="t">timestamp</td><td>UTC timestamp of DLT confirmation</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>AuditReport</h3>
      <p>
        Tracks the generation lifecycle of compliance documents. Created when an auditor
        requests a Compliance Report. The <code>file_path</code> and <code>download_url</code>
        are set once the report is generated (synchronously in pilot mode; via Sidekiq job
        in production).
      </p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">id</td><td class="t">uuid</td><td>Primary key — returned as <code>report_id</code> in API response</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">report_type</td><td class="t">enum</td><td><code>compliance</code> | <code>full_export</code> | <code>custom</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">generated_by</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Operator ID of the auditor who requested the report</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">jurisdiction</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Jurisdiction scope applied to the report</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">parameters</td><td class="t">jsonb</td><td>Filter parameters used: <code>{from, to, jurisdiction, status, operator_id}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">file_path</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Server-side path to the generated document</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">download_url</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Relative URL for the Qt client to download the PDF</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">generated_at</td><td class="t">timestamp</td><td>Time the document was produced</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>IssuerKey (shared)</h3>
      <p>
        Ed25519 public keys registered to central banks. Used by <code>Audit::SignatureVerificationService</code>
        to verify event signatures. <strong>No private key is ever accessed from this tab</strong> — the
        service reads only <code>public_key</code> (or its <code>public_key_b64url</code> accessor).
        Key status must be <code>active</code> for verification to proceed.
      </p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Used by Audit tab</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">key_id</td><td><span class="dp-badge green">YES</span></td><td>Looked up via <code>issuer_key_id</code> in event payload</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">public_key</td><td><span class="dp-badge green">YES</span></td><td>Decoded via <code>public_key_b64url</code> accessor (JWK or raw Base64URL)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">status</td><td><span class="dp-badge green">YES</span></td><td>Must be <code>active</code> — revoked keys return verification failure</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">private_key_b64url</td><td><span class="dp-badge red">NEVER</span></td><td>Private key is never read in the Audit tab — signing is Issuance-only</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>Service Layer</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Service</th><th>File</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>Audit::EventQueryService</code></td><td>app/services/audit/event_query_service.rb</td><td>Applies filter params to <code>AuditEvent</code> scope; paginates; returns <code>as_api_json</code> array</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Audit::EventDetailsService</code></td><td>app/services/audit/event_details_service.rb</td><td>Loads a single event by <code>id</code> with full payload including authorizers</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Audit::ExportService</code></td><td>app/services/audit/export_service.rb</td><td>Generates CSV up to 5,000 rows from the current filter scope</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Audit::SignatureVerificationService</code></td><td>app/services/audit/signature_verification_service.rb</td><td>Ed25519 verify via <code>RbNaCl</code> — reads only <code>IssuerKey#public_key_b64url</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Audit::ComplianceReportService</code></td><td>app/services/audit/compliance_report_service.rb</td><td>Creates <code>AuditReport</code> record; enqueues <code>AuditReportGeneratorJob</code> if Sidekiq present</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Audit::ReportDownloadService</code></td><td>app/services/audit/report_download_service.rb</td><td>Resolves report by ID; returns <code>download_url</code> for Qt client</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Audit::SnapshotAnchorService</code></td><td>app/services/audit/snapshot_anchor_service.rb</td><td>Builds SHA-256 chain digest; creates <code>AuditSnapshot</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Audit::EventHashingService</code></td><td>app/services/audit/event_hashing_service.rb</td><td>Deterministic SHA-256 over canonical event fields — used at event creation time</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>
    </div>

    <%# ── §3 Pane-by-Pane Logic ───────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="pane-logic">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§3</div>
        <h2>Pane-by-Pane Logic &amp; Behavior</h2>
      </div>

      <h3>Left Pane — Forensic Filters &amp; Health (240 px sidebar)</h3>

      <h4>Monetary Health Ribbon</h4>
      <p>
        The health ribbon populates on tab entry via
        <code>GET /api/v2/audit/health_metrics?jurisdiction={selected}</code>.
        It refreshes automatically when the jurisdiction filter changes. Three tiles:
      </p>

      <div class="dp-health-bar">
        <div class="dp-health-tile">
          <div class="ht-label">Supply Integrity</div>
          <div class="ht-value ok">99.2%</div>
          <div class="ht-sub">Events succeeded / total</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-health-tile">
          <div class="ht-label">Pending Anchorings</div>
          <div class="ht-value warn">3</div>
