    <%# ── §4 UI Behavior ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="ui-behavior">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§4</div>
        <h2>UI Behavior &amp; State Rules</h2>
      </div>

      <h3>Tab Initialization Sequence</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Step</th><th>Method</th><th>What happens</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>1</td><td><code>setupTables()</code></td><td>Sets column headers, selection policy, alternating row colors on both tables</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2</td><td><code>connectSignals()</code></td><td>Wires all buttons, row-selection signals, and table context menu policies</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3</td><td><code>loadHealthMetrics()</code></td><td><code>GET /api/v2/audit/health_metrics</code> — populates Supply Integrity, Pending, Alerts ribbon</td></tr>
          <tr><td>4</td><td><code>loadEvents()</code></td><td><code>GET /api/v2/audit/events</code> (no filters) — populates both tables</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>Event Details Clear Rules</h3>
      <p>
        <code>clearEventDetails()</code> is called when:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>btnAudApplyFilter</code> is clicked (new filter clears stale selection)</li>
        <li>The table is refreshed and the previously selected row no longer exists</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        All detail labels revert to <code>—</code>, text fields are cleared, and the HSM badge
        resets to neutral grey. <code>m_selectedEventId</code> is cleared.
      </p>

      <h3>Table Column Width Strategy</h3>
      <p>
        <code>horizontalHeader()-&gt;setStretchLastSection(true)</code> is set on both tables.
        This means the Amount / Status column stretches to fill remaining width. For the top table,
        the Timestamp column should be set to a fixed minimum of 155 px to prevent truncation.
      </p>

      <h3>Health Ribbon Colour Transitions</h3>
      <p>
        The three health labels use Qt <code>setStyleSheet()</code> applied on every API response.
        Pending Verifications: amber if &gt; 0, blue if 0. Active Alerts: green if 0, amber if 1–3,
        red if &gt; 3. Supply Integrity: green ≥ 99%, amber 95–99%, red &lt; 95%.
      </p>

      <h3>Compliance Report Workflow (PDF Download Flow)</h3>
      <p>
        The PDF download is a two-step process:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Auditor selects a report type in <code>cmbAudReportType</code> and clicks
            <strong>Generate Compliance Report</strong>. Rails creates an <code>AuditReport</code>
            record and returns the <code>report_id</code>. Qt stores this in <code>m_lastReportId</code>.</li>
        <li>Auditor clicks <strong>Generate Certified Audit Statement</strong>
            (<code>btnAudExportPdf</code>). Qt calls
            <code>GET /api/v2/audit/reports/{m_lastReportId}/download</code>
            and presents a save-file dialog. The <code>Last Export</code> label is stamped with
            the current timestamp.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        If <code>m_lastReportId</code> is empty when the PDF button is clicked, a
        <code>QMessageBox::information</code> prompts: <em>"Generate a compliance report first."</em>
      </p>

      <h3>Snapshot Anchor Post-Action</h3>
      <p>
        After a successful anchor, <code>lblAudSnapshotHashVal</code> is updated with the
        <code>snapshot_hash</code> from the response. A <code>QMessageBox</code> shows the hash
        and DLT tx ID. The health metrics ribbon is <em>not</em> auto-refreshed — the auditor
        must click Refresh to see the updated Pending Anchorings count.
      </p>
    </div>

    <%# ── §5 User Flow ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
